Module kivakit.interfaces
Package com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.naming

Interface NamedObject

All Superinterfaces:
Nameable
public interface NamedObject extends Nameable
An object with a programmatic name. An object that is a NamedObject differs from an object that is Named in that its name is meant for use by programmers and not end users. If objectName() is not implemented, a synthetic name for the object is created with syntheticName(Object).

By default, NamedObjects are not Nameable unless the object implementing this interface allows it.

Author:
jonathanl (shibo)
